						               													<description>An operational level game in postcard size/format, of the August 7-13 1944 German counter-offensive trying to break through Mortain and neighboring towns (down in &amp;quot;Normandy's Switzerland&amp;quot;) to get westward to Avranches on the sea to cut off supplies and units to Patton's 3rd Army pouring through it into Brittany and the rest of France.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;6 divisions on each side, plus the heroic 2nd Battalion, 120th Infantry Regiment, 30th (Old Hickory, National Guard) Division which successfully held out surrounded atop Hill 317 above Mortain for 6 days.  7 one-day turns, as historically.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;50% strategic possibility of treacherously patriotic anti-Hitler conspirator General der Panzertruppen Gerhard Graf von Schwerin as historically - and he survived the SS and the war! - holding back 116.PzDiv for the crucial first 2 days, in which case victory for the German player is instead just cutting 1st Army's nearer north-south route to get units down and around to the east to form the southern flank of the Falaise Pocket which decimated the German Army in the West, historically.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Factor differential plus press-your-luck Pressed Attack and/or Desperate Defense - Special Factor - combat mechanics which make it excellent for solitaire play.&amp;#10;U.S. infantry division Deployment doubling their strengths for both artillery-supported defense *and attack*.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Allied RAF 84 Group Typhoons and 303rd Wing P-47 Thunderbolts to aerially torment the Germans.&amp;#10;Subtle Disruption Recovery phase variation to simulate veteran German units' operational resilience.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Anyone is free to print off as many copies as they like in A5/5x8 or A6/4x6 postcard format, to mail/give to family and friends, as long as they keep my copyright statement and the Dedication.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For your one own personal copy, you will want to photo-copy enlarge the units to A4/8.5x11 and the map to A3/11x17 ... or larger, if you want.  Anyone wanting to *publish* a (boxed?) large format edition of the game must license that right from me.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;FIENDISH little game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
